{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idcf8a9599-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0","identifier":"/us/usc/t48/s1707"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1707"},"text":"§ 1707.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Payment of rents, royalties, and fees to local government","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"On and after the date of enactment of this Act, all rents, royalties, or fees from leases, permits, or use rights, issued prior to such date of enactment by the United States with respect to the land conveyed by this Act, or by the amendment made by this Act, and rights of action for damages for trespass occupancies of such lands shall accrue and belong to the appropriate local government under whose jurisdiction the land is located.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idcf8a959a-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/93/435/s4"},"text":"Pub. L. 93–435, § 4","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1974-10-05"},"text":"Oct. 5, 1974","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/88/1212"},"text":"88 Stat. 1212","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idcf8a959b-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idcf8a959c-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"idcf8a959d-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Date of enactment, referred to in text, is the date of enactment of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/93/435"},"text":"Pub. L. 93–435","children":[],"tail":", which was approved "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1974-10-05"},"text":"Oct. 5, 1974","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"This Act, referred to in text, is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/93/435"},"text":"Pub. L. 93–435","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1974-10-05"},"text":"Oct. 5, 1974","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/88/1210"},"text":"88 Stat. 1210","children":[],"tail":", which enacted sections 1705 to 1708 of this title, amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t48/s1545"},"text":"section 1545 of this title","children":[],"tail":", and repealed sections 1701 to 1703 of this title. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Tables."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The amendment made by this Act, referred to in text, means the amendment made by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/93/435/s3"},"text":"section 3 of Pub. L. 93–435","children":[],"tail":" to "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t48/s1545/b"},"text":"section 1545(b) of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idcf8a959e-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"idcf8a959f-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References to “Date of Enactment”","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"For the purposes of the amendment made by subsection (a) of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":